org.opengis.cite.securityclient10.httpServer

Class TestServer

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.opengis.cite.securityclient10.httpServer.TestServer

  • public class TestServer
extends Object
    A wrapper class around the Jetty Server class. This adds functionality for the testing suite for adding/removing servlets to capture test client requests.

      • registerHandler

        public void registerHandler(String path,
                            ServerOptions serverOptions)
                     throws Exception
        Create a new ServletContextHandler for the given `path`, and create a shared handler block boolean. The boolean will be used by the waitForRequest thread to delay until the request is fulfilled or a timeout is hit. The Handler will catch requests to `path`, and to `path/*` where `*` is a wildcard.
        Parameters:
        path - HTTP path to dynamically add to the embedded server
        serverOptions - ServerOptions Object with options for the type of OWS to emulate, will determine which capabilities document will be presented to the client
        Throws:
        Exception - Exception if context could not be started

      • shutdown

        public void shutdown()
              throws Exception
        Shut down the embedded server. This will force close any open HTTP connections.
        Throws:
        Exception - for any errors shutting down the embedded server

      • unregisterHandler

        public void unregisterHandler(String path)
                       throws org.opengis.cite.servlet.ServletException
        Iterate through the registered ServletContextHandler instances on this server for the first one to have a mapping matching `path`, and if found then that ServletContextHandler is removed. If no match is found then nothing is done.
        Parameters:
        path - HTTP path to dynamically remove from the embedded server
        Throws:
        org.opengis.cite.servlet.ServletException - For any errors removing a servlet context handler

      • waitForRequest

        public void waitForRequest(String path)
                    throws InterruptedException,
                           ExecutionException
        Block the thread until a request is received, or the timeout is hit.
        Parameters:
        path - The unique code associated with the thread created to wait for the servlet activation
        Throws:
        InterruptedException - For any errors caused by the waiting thread being interrupted
        ExecutionException - For any errors caused by the waiting thread having an exception
